Bactrocera cucurbitae
(listed as
Dacus cucurbitae
) was recovered from pigeon pea (
C. cajan
) which originated from a port in Hawaii and was intercepted at a port in California (1 interception in non-entry host) between 1 July 1946 and 30 June 1947 (number of individuals recovered and life stages not reported). Taxonomic identification was done by entomologists of the Bureau of Entomology and Plant Quarantine, USDA.

